net.myorb.math.expressions

Class ArrayFunction<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.myorb.math.expressions.ArrayFunction<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type on which operations are to be executed
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BuiltInArrayAbstractions

    public class ArrayFunction<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    treat array as function of domain specified in metadata. extrapolation of function values between array elements allows function to appear continuous. other functionalities available include derivative, integral, charting, and interpolation. an interval function allows a sub-domain of a function to be evaluated atonomously.
    Author:
    Michael Druckman

      • computeXaxisOffset

        public T computeXaxisOffset(T x,
                            T delta,
                            T lo)
        compute the x-axis offset from the beginning of the array. the computed offset into the array will be a real value which identifies an element and an offset from that element. the characteristic of the value is the full element count, the mantissa is a fraction of the element difference. the mapping between the two elements is assumed to be a linear equivalence, this will be an error source.
        Parameters:
        x - the value on the x-axis the function is to be evaluated at
        delta - the x-axis value increment between array elements
        lo - the lowest x-axis value of the domain constraint
        Returns:
        the computed x-axis offset
